A previously healthy 30-year-old man presented with sudden and intense back pain after lifting a heavy object. Radiological investigation demonstrated an L4 burst fracture with presence of bone fragments in the spinal canal (Fig. <xref ref-type="fig" rid="rjw063f01">1</xref>). Clinical examination was normal except for a mild left foot numbness. His routine laboratory assessment revealed hypochromic microcytic anemia.
